can  you fix the address format
Here's a better format for the address that handles optional fields properly:

```tsx
address: formatAddress(studio),
```

Then add this helper function at the top of your file:

```tsx
const formatAddress = (studio: any) => {
  const parts = [];

  if (studio.address) parts.push(studio.address);
  if (studio.city) parts.push(studio.city);

  const regionParts = [];
  if (studio.stateName) regionParts.push(studio.stateName);
  if (studio.postalCode) regionParts.push(studio.postalCode);

  if (regionParts.length > 0) {
    parts.push(regionParts.join(' '));
  }

  if (studio.countryName) parts.push(studio.countryName);

  return parts.join(', ');
};
```

This will format the address like:
- "123 Main St, New York, New York 10001, United States"

The function handles cases where some fields might be missing, and puts the country at the end which is a more standard international format. It also prevents having empty commas if some fields are missing.
