i want to get the return type of enhanceStudiosWithLocationNames
To get the return type of `enhanceStudiosWithLocationNames`, use this instead:

```ts
// Define the type for an enhanced studio
export type EnhancedStudio = ReturnType<typeof enhanceStudioWithLocationNames>;

// Define the type for an array of enhanced studios
export type EnhancedStudios = ReturnType<typeof enhanceStudiosWithLocationNames>;
```

This uses TypeScript's utility type `ReturnType` to extract the return type of the function. 

For `enhanceStudioWithLocationNames`, it will give you:
`T & { countryName?: string; stateName?: string }`

For `enhanceStudiosWithLocationNames`, it will give you:
`Array<T & { countryName?: string; stateName?: string }>`

You can use these types elsewhere in your code when you need to reference the enhanced studio objects.
